oncogenic mutations in KRAS impair its GTPase activity,

gression.56 KRAS mutations are primarily single base missense

In this study，we addressed this unmet need to degrade
KRASGI2D by designingand synthesizing a novel seriesof
PROTACs, which combine KRAsG12D inhibitors with CRBN E3
ligase ligands to achieve targeted degradation of the
oncoprotein. Among these, ZJK-8o7 emerged as a standout
candidate, demonstrating exceptional selectivity and potency in
AsPC-1 pancreatic cancer cel line. Mechanistically， ZJK-807
effectively recruited CRBN E3 ligase to
ubiquitination and subsequent proteasomal degradation, there-
by suppressing downstream oncogenic signaling pathways. In
addition to its potent degradation activity, ZJK-807 exhibited
inhibiting the growth of KRAsG12D-driven cancer cels. In vivo,
xenograft model resulted in substantial tumor growth inhibition
minimal systemic toxicity. ZJK-807_ also demonstrated anti-
resistance properties against KRAsGi2D secondary mutation.
These findings highlight the therapeutic potential of ZJK-807 as
to overcome the limitations of traditional KRAS inhibitors.
